<div class="postright">
<h3>Re: Parrot OS - Persistence + Updates + Ram Mode</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>if you use the ram mode the whole pendrive is copied in ram thanks to a particular set of boot parameters</p><p>when you use the persistence boot option you are passing to your kernel a completely different set of parameters</p><br/><p>the persistence doesn&#039;t work for you when you boot from the ram option because the ram option does not pass the &quot;persistence&quot; parameter to the kernel</p><br/><p>anyway it is discouraged to do heavy system upgrades on a live system with persistence as it slows down the system and it doesn&#039;t allow you to do kernel upgrades</p>
</div>
<div class="postsignature postmsg"><hr/><p>Lorenzo &quot;Palinuro&quot; Faletra - Parrot Security</p><p>GPG FINGERPRINT: B350 5059 3C2F 7656 40E6 DDDB 97CA A129 F4C6 B9A4<br/>GPG Info: <a href="https://pgp.mit.edu/pks/lookup?op=vindex&amp;search=0x97CAA129F4C6B9A4" rel="nofollow">http://pgp.mit.edu/pks/lookup?op=vindex … 29F4C6B9A4</a><br/>GPG Key: <a href="https://pgp.mit.edu/pks/lookup?op=get&amp;search=0x97CAA129F4C6B9A4" rel="nofollow">http://pgp.mit.edu/pks/lookup?op=get&amp;se … 29F4C6B9A4</a></p></div>
